docs.abstract: For the second time in eight days the Vermont senator addressed complaints from former staff members that women in his campaign were mistreated, calling it “unacceptable.’’
docs.snippet: For the second time in eight days the Vermont senator addressed complaints from former staff members that women in his campaign were mistreated, calling it “unacceptable.’’
docs.lead_paragraph: For a second time in eight days, Senator Bernie Sanders apologized to women on his 2016 presidential campaign, as he seeks to put behind him a series of damaging reports about the mistreatment of female staff members that threatens to undercut another likely White House bid.

headline.main: Bernie Sanders Apologizes Again to Women Who Were Mistreated in 2016 Campaign
headline.print_headline: 2nd Apology  By Sanders Over Claims Of Sexism

headline.main: On Politics: The Biggest Stories of the Week

docs.abstract: Mr. Sanders has not yet told advisers he intends to pursue another White House bid. But if he does, he will encounter a vastly different landscape than that of 2016.
docs.snippet: Mr. Sanders has not yet told advisers he intends to pursue another White House bid. But if he does, he will encounter a vastly different landscape than that of 2016.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Some of his top congressional supporters won’t commit to backing him if he runs for president again — and two may join the 2020 race themselves. A handful of former aides might work for other candidates. And Bernie Sanders’s initial standing in Iowa polls is well below the 49.6 percent he captured in nearly defeating Hillary Clinton there in 2016.

headline.main: For Bernie Sanders, Holding Onto Support May Be Hard in a 2020 Bid
headline.print_headline: Support Turns Noncommittal As Sanders Weighs 2020 Run

byline.original: By Jonathan Martin and Sydney Ember

docs.abstract: A printing error improperly left off about 119,000 names, forcing many voters to cast provisional ballots. No specific reason for the mistake was immediately known.
docs.snippet: A printing error improperly left off about 119,000 names, forcing many voters to cast provisional ballots. No specific reason for the mistake was immediately known.
docs.lead_paragraph: COSTA MESA, Calif. — A printing error improperly left about 119,000 names off voting rosters in Los Angeles County, forcing many to cast provisional ballots, prolonging the counting and election results in the state’s most populous county.

headline.main: Thousands of Voters Were Left Off Primary Day Rolls in Los Angeles

docs.abstract: More than just a flashback to 2000, the Florida recount is an ominous dry run for messaging about vote-stealing that will further erode confidence in the election process.
docs.snippet: More than just a flashback to 2000, the Florida recount is an ominous dry run for messaging about vote-stealing that will further erode confidence in the election process.
docs.lead_paragraph: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. — The chaotic images out of Florida’s election recount last week — the brigade of Washington lawyers, the déjà vu meltdown of the tallying in Broward County, the vitriolic charges and countercharges — have prompted flashbacks among the electorate of the 2000 presidential election.

headline.main: Charges of Vote Stealing in Florida Portend More Distrust in System for 2020
headline.print_headline: Vitriol Over Vote-Stealing Charges Sets a Troubling Tone for 2020

byline.original: By Glenn Thrush and Jeremy W. Peters

docs.abstract: Mr. Buttigieg has confronted evangelicals like Vice President Mike Pence, questioning the moral authority of religious leaders who have stayed silent on President Trump’s conduct.
docs.snippet: Mr. Buttigieg has confronted evangelicals like Vice President Mike Pence, questioning the moral authority of religious leaders who have stayed silent on President Trump’s conduct.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As a religious gay man who believes his party has ceded discussion of religion and spirituality to Republicans, Pete Buttigieg, a Democratic candidate for president, is talking about God and sexuality in an unconventional way: He is using the language of faith to confront the Christian right on territory they have long claimed as their own.

headline.main: Pete Buttigieg, Gay and Christian, Challenges Religious Right on Their Own Turf
headline.print_headline: Gay and Christian, a 2020 Contender Challenges the Religious Right
